<br>
"Well done, a most interesting tale. Tell me, a warrior such as you will surely have a keep-sake piece of armor or favourite charm of some sort ?"<br>
<i>What is your favourite your item/gear you own?</i><br>
<br>
In response, Elhimac pushed aside the folds of his cloak and drew forth his sword from the scabbard at his side. As the blade followed the hilt, Piqa noted that the blade was half again as long as the scabbard and twice as wide. How he managed to fit it in the scabbard was beyond her. Piqa guessed magic.<br>
The sword was laid on the table with a sound like far-off lightning splitting a tree in two. Piqa noted that the volume of background conversation dropped several levels as curious and frightened bar patrons stole uneasy glances at the naked blade. <br>
<br>
"This is my weapon of choice. It has been with me from an early age, and though deadlier weapons and more flashy pieces of armor exist, I will wield none but this Rune-encrusted Sword." The blade was made of a bluish sort of metal and faint runes could be made out near the hilt and the tip.<br>
<br>
"It seems a most worthy blade for you, is there some tale associated with it, or how it came into your possession perhaps ?" Piqa asked, hoping for a possible breach in the walls that so vigorously protected Elhimac's past.<br>
<br>
"I know none of its history before it came into my possession, but I acquired it in a rather amusing way." Sensing a tale, Piqa dipped her quill in the inkwell and took a new piece of paper.<br>
<br>
"Oh it is nothing much, but I came upon this blade in a merchants scrap pile. It was tarnished and encrusted with filth, so it resembled nothing so much as an apprentice smith's first tentative try in the art of smiting. I chanced to pick it up and instantly felt the excellent balance that the blade possessed, rusted and dirty through it was. On a spur of the moment, I went to the vendor and told him I desired this blade for its metal, explaining that I would melt it down. We haggled a bit and he finally let me have it for the ridiculous price of 7 Platinum Wyrms! <br>
I cleaned the blade, sharpened it and also discovered the runes that adorn it. Their meaning is lost, and their significance can only be guessed at, but I have little doubt that they mark the blade as the work of a master smith from ages past. Certainty the blade compares favourably with the finest many armories has to offer."<br>
 <br>
<br>
"Surely that blade would have drawn the blood of your foes in many a distant realm, tell me, is there any particular place that you long for in significant ways ?"<br>
<i>What is your favourite hunting ground?</i><br>
<br>
"Neriak is my home." He answered simply.<br>
<br>
"Yes, but…" Piqa began, somewhat baffled<br>
<br>
Elhimac let out a short mocking laugh. "Ms Ravenheart, surely you understand that my home is where I belong. It was where I was born and where I was raised. How could I long for any other place ? <br>
And as for spilling blood, duty has sent me over most of the world, from the vast plains of Karana, the turbulent seas the separate the continents to new and savage frontiers. And not many of these places have been friendly." His last sentence carried a twinge of disdain, or possibly regret, Piqa noticed.<br>
<br>
 "Well said, no place like home indeed. I can't imagine that someone as clever as you have made many mistakes in your career, but can you perhaps indulge my whim of revealing pieces of the mortal beneath the reputation ?" Piqa asked and leaned forward in a friendly sarcastic way, hoping that her phrasing would make it seem to be her flaw that was the greater for wanting to expose a weakness or two.<br>
 <i>What was your silliest newbie moment?</i><br>
<br>
Elhimac regarded her for a trifle longer than necessary before replying: "Mistakes I have made of course, I am not divine. But few, if any, of them have been more than a temporary lapse that was easily corrected. None worthy of note or mirth." Piqa was not quite sure she believed him in this, but even her sharp well-trained eyes could not make out the marks of a concealed truth upon his face.   <br>
<br>
"Very well then." She jotted down a few notes to avoid an awkward pause while she collected herself for the next question. "Many of my clients have mentors or other persons who they have felt have inspired them, have you likewise have had any inspirational friends ?"<br>
<i>Who inspired you as a youngster?</i><br>
<br>
He leaned back and stared out at nothing in particular and Piqa almost got the impression that he had not heard her, impossible though it might seem. She was just about to repeat herself when he gave a short laugh with startled her even more than the ironic smile that spread across his lips.<br>
<br>
"I would most certainly not call her a friend." He began, looking Piqa into the eye once more. "But I can say in all truth that 'High Seat' Cimmarose of House Winterblood as she styles herself, have had a more than usual impact upon my career. She is uncommonly shrewd in her leadership and none should know better than I, being her mortal enemy. I have often made great use of her example.<br>
As for others, my inspiration comes mainly from leaders rather than fighters, names such as Tgcid, Utnayan and others of their kind. Though I am sure they are from before your time." <br>
   <br>
Piqa shuffled her noted a bit in preparation for her next barrage of questions. These ones dealt with finances and people had been know to get angry when she plied into them. She considered these the most delicate questions hence they were relegated to late in the interview, when the client was hopefully at ease, drunk or both. Unfortunately, Elhimac seemed to be neither.<br>
<br>
"I have heard of their names a bit. Tell me Commander, are you a rich person ?"<br>
<i>What's the most pp you have ever had at one time?</i><br>
 <br>
"Not compared to so many others," he said with perfect ease. "While I will never lack for anything, luxury of many sorts are beyond my personal finances, as well it should be. Rarely will my liquid fortune exceed 500 Wyrms." He didn't seem the least disturbed by this, but compared to so many others Piqa knew who held high positions, this was a shockingly meagre sum. <br>
 <br>
"Perhaps it is due to a ill-fortuned trade or some such ?" Piqa asked with friendly interest, like a friend might ask to the health of a distant cousin.<br>
<i>What's the worst trade you ever got suckered into?</i><br>
 <br>
"No" he said with neither hesitation nor emotion. "Money has simply not captured my interest, certainty not in the matter of misers that hoard their coins like they were the life-blood of the world." He swallowed the last few drops of his drink and awaited her next assault.<br>
 <br>
"I can imagine you have seen many strange things and beheld wondrous marvels, would you perhaps enlighten me with what creature you find the strangest, here in the closing hours of our interview ?" And indeed the night was coming to a close, time had seemed to fly by and the tavern was already more empty than full. <br>
<i>What mob is the coolest looking you've ever seen/fought?</i><br>
 <br>
"Aye, this is a strange world we live in. I have seen things that should have no right to live given rational thought. Strangest of all I must consider the Fungusmen of Innuthule Swamp, there is something entirely unnatural about them, they have neither eyes nor ears and their bodies are made of soft mould or fungus, yet they walk like men and prey upon the living. Nature has a vast bestiary indeed; the living cactus plants in Kunark are a sight to be seen. As are the floating eyes of the Beholder King, the mechanical constructs of the Gnomes and many others."<br>
<br>
Fixing Elhimac with a well-rehearsed look that was part amusement and part secrecy, Piqa asked: "Have you ever been afraid Commander ?"<br>
<i>What are the scariest/most nerve-wracking moments you've had in EQ?</i><br>
<br>
He returned her expression with a slight smile and the same arching of the eyebrows "I wish I could say no, but I would be lying if I did. Fear is as much part of me as of any other person. I fear for my life and health before any battle, I fear for my reputation were I to commit a grave error, I fear for the unknown abyss that awaits us all in the end, I fear all that mortals fear. But;" he held up a warning finger " I can master my fear."<br>
 <br>
Piqa had never really expected any other reply, though it was a surprise to hear him admit it all. She smiled knowingly and gazed at her empty mug. It had been a long night. The last few patrons were already being hustled out the door and the manager was casting longing glances at Piqa's table and the one with Elhimac's bodyguards. <br>
She rose to her feet while surveying them and almost felt pity for his two bodyguards. They still sat in the same watchful positions that they had taken since the evening began, never being offered as much as a mug of ale, nor even a kind look but surrounded by a perpetual aura of grim watchfulness. <br>
Piqa wondered what she had missed, what hidden quality it was that Commander Elhimac possessed, that could make people such as his two bodyguards follow him without the slightest doubt or care for themselves.<br>
<br>
"One last thing." She said as he gathered his cloak about him and prepared to set off. "What accomplishment are you the proudest of Commander Elhimac ?"  <br>
<i>What accomplishment in game are you the proudest of so far?</i><br>
<br>
He held her gaze for a long time then turned away to his guards who rose and fell in besides him. They were halfway to the door before he finally answered in that clear-carrying voice: "That I have made a difference." <br>
